{"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ScreenReader\/recognizeText()","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ScreenReader\/waitForText(_:timeout:)"],"generated":true,"anchor":"Instance-Methods","title":"Instance Methods"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ScreenReader","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/screenreader"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"metadata":{"title":"ScreenReader","symbolKind":"protocol","roleHeading":"Protocol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ScreenReader"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ScreenReader"}],"externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit12ScreenReaderP","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ScreenReader"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Sendable","preciseIdentifier":"s:s8SendableP"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Implement this protocol to provide screen capture and OCR"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for screen-aware Setup Assistant automation. The screen reader"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"enables the automation executor to wait for specific text to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"appear on the VM display before proceeding, replacing fixed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"timing delays with deterministic screen state checks."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Design","text":"Design","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This follows the approach used by"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/cirruslabs\/tart","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"which uses Apple’s Vision framework to recognize text on the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"VM screen and drive Setup Assistant navigation based on what"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is actually visible rather than elapsed time."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Architecture","text":"Architecture","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The protocol lives in SpooktacularKit (no AppKit or Vision"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"imports) so it can be referenced from any target. The concrete"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"implementation ("},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"VZScreenReader"},{"type":"text","text":") lives in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"spook"},{"type":"text","text":" CLI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"target where AppKit and Vision are available."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Example","text":"Example","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["let reader: ScreenReader = VZScreenReader(vmView: view)","let match = try await reader.waitForText(\"Continue\", timeout: 60)","print(\"Found '\\(match.text)' at \\(match.boundingBox)\")"],"type":"codeListing"}],"kind":"content"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/s8SendableP","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/s16SendableMetatypeP"],"type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Reads text from a virtual machine’s display.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/s8SendableP":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/Spo